What an experience. I loved how clean the restaurant is above all. Color is added to black and white decor with the addition of fresh fruits, veg, food and teas.  I love that we can try so many different things in one plate and their parking lot makes it easy to grab a box to eat in the car.  The rice and peas are beyond perfection. Tried the quinoa And didn’t love it.  Boiled provisions are my fav. The steamed veggies are colorful and perfectly cooked. I got to add crunchy raw veg on top my plate at the end. Don’t forget to ask for plantain, I did :( my main was the chana curry which was soooooo good.  They had akee patty’s which I will try next time and my ginger tea was so strong, I went home and made three cups out of it.  I waited a for a slice of Mac and cheese. It was good but DEF which needs work. there was not much flavor besides the top.  Verdure is strong. Love it and will be back.
